  "text": "To determine the impact of autologous nAbs on antiviral control and viral evolution, this group used quantitative polymerase chain reaction to track fluctuations of wild-type and emerging quasispecies or viral variants [CITATION_1] . This group was able to demonstrate that after the appearance of the first nAb wave, the overall viral load declined consistent with the decline in the wild-type viral variant levels. This was followed by the emergence of an escape variant that then outcompeted the wildtype isolate, resulting in a slight increase in the overall viral load. This observed \"blip\" in overall viral load in parallel with antibody-induced emergence of alternate viral quasispecies suggests that similar fluctuations in viral load may reflect the emergence and disappearance of viral variants under immune pressure.",
